java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class SurfacePatchLimitsDialog
extends javax.swing.JDialog
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener

This helper class provides a dialog for updating point limits in SurfacePatches being edited by a SurfacePatchDialog editor. Pressing the OK button will cause the class to check the SurfacePatchEditor dialog textFields for errors. If no errors are found, the new limits are set in the SurfacePatchDialog object. If an error is found, the dialog box will stay open. Pressing the Cancel button will hide and unload the dialog.
